9:
Exactly. The Guild controls all
transactions in Palpebra, which can
be very inconvenient... Especially for
someone like me.
10:
To them I'm just an unfamiliar,
suspicious outsider. The fact that I
never take off my metal mask
certainly doesn't help, either.
14:
I'm pretty sure they'd want even less
to do with you if you took off your
whole face...
17:
Regardless, I had to make do with
less than conventional routes of
business. That's where I met
Procheon.
20:
I swear I had no hand in what he's
done today. Just because I don't
follow the rules, doesn't mean I don't
have my own personal policies.
22:
That's why I won't stand idly by while
he brainwashes a little girl and
threatens all the innocents in this
city.
29:
I wish I could have prevented this
whole mess in the first place,
considering I had my suspicions
about him from the start...
31:
At the very least, the tracker I stuck
on him will finally prove useful.
37:
We should hurry. The deeper he
goes, the harder it'll be to locate his
signal.
41: Are you kidding me? Not again!
45:
Seems like Procheon's calling on
more of his dragon pals...
48:
I'm amazed he can do that from the
inside of the Kaleidoscope.
53:
We'll split into two groups—one to
protect the city, and the other to
chase down that thief.
57:
With Enlil in my hand, I can fight any
airborne foe. I'll remain behind and
keep watch over the city.
60:
Are you sure? Wasn't it your job to
apprehend him?
63:
The Farlands are at fault for aiding
him in the first place.
66:
Therefore, it falls to me to protect
the victims of our mistake.
70:
I have faith that you can stop him in
my place.
79:
I should probably stay to fight the
dragons too... Bring the kid home,
you hear?
84:
Cecilia and I will join the chase—and
don't try to talk me out of it!
87:
We'll do everything we can to save
Arum!
97:
And you'll need me to follow the
tracker's signal. Looks like our teams
are decided!
105:
When we do, you better give her
your best apology.
110:
Well, there's probably no good way
to break the bad news, but... I've lost
him!
114:
Are you joking? You said you could
track him down!
118:
I-I wasn't lying! His signal abruptly
vanished—which is very strange,
now that I mention it!
121:
You said Procheon's a Star Augur,
right? He must have some tricky
powers up his sleeves then.
126:
I am sorry to disappoint, but I wasn't
privy to much information regarding
the priests.
130:
They were pretty powerful figures in
your old world, right?
134:
Lady Phiria and I lived in a citadel
deep within a mountain range
shrouded by fog. It was a place far
smaller than Palpebra.
136:
The Star Augurs were the
unquestioned leaders there—priests
who ruled over our lives. It was my
family's duty as knights to protect
them.
138:
As an obedient servant, there was
much I didn't know, including what
lay in the world beyond the
mountains.
143:
I know what that's like. We fiends
were also told nothing, except "Hey,
those are the enemies, now fight
them!"
147:
Lady Phiria was chosen by the Star
Augurs to be their oracle... I,
however, have only been in her
service for the past three years.
152:
I was a little girl when they brought
me to their facility and trapped me
there.
155:
But I wasn't the only child. There
were so many of us, but one by one,
they disappeared...
157:
I remained, because... I was a
success. That's what they called me.
164:
Then one day, they told us it was
time to fulfill our roles. We were sent
to the battlefield.
166:
I don't remember much of our
departure from the mountains, as
they put us into a deep sleep
beforehand.
169:
But once we left... We were able to
learn of the world outside. All its
people—the beautiful longears, the
beastfolk... the fiends and daemons...
172:
That was also around the time we
met Sir Gerard.
182:
Er, if you're talking about, well... I'm
not sure how much I should say...
186: Right, right... I think I get it.
191:
...You know, your story sounds a lot
like Arum's.
193:
She was also "chosen" to be used as
a weapon against others—humans,
in her case.
198:
I'm sorry... If we had spoken up
sooner, maybe...
202:
You've got nothing to apologize for.
Keep your sympathy to yourself too.
204:
Remember what I said before? This
is how things are—all because we
never knew the whole story... Never
tried to learn it either.
207:
All I care about now is saving Arum,
everything else be damned.
210:
I'll do whatever I have to, and use
whoever I have to...
214:
But... You have my thanks for
choosing to be here.
218:
Use us however you like. We'll do our
part.
226:
There he is! How convenient he
decided to reappear now of all
times.
227:
This must be his idea of inviting us
over for tea. I bet he's already set
the table and everything.
231: Even if it's a trap, we still have to go.
236:
Well then, shall we get this party
started?
